    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen doing undo and redo neovim shows messages like\n\n```\n1 line less; before #1  1 second ago\n```\n\nThere is no way to hide these messages. I personally think the messages are not very useful, except when the message is stating that \"Already at oldest change\" or \"Already at newest change\".\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt would be nice to have an option, e.g. as part of `shortmess`, that 1) fully disables the undo/redo messages, and/or 2) disables all undo/redo messages except messages indicating oldest/newest change.\n\nFor context: I'm raising this feature request from the discussion in [this reddit thread](https://www.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/1spm4x6/comment/oh27yfp/).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "As this happens in Vim, too, and `shortmess` is a Vim option, I would recommend opening this at vim/vim so we can port the patch without diverging. (+1, this fits well into `shortmess`.)",
